Package: htpc-remote
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Darren Naidoo <dnaidoo621@users.noreply.github.com>
Depends: python3 (>= 3.9), python3-gi, python3-gi-cairo, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, xdotool
Pre-Depends: python3-pip, python3-venv
Recommends: wtype, brightnessctl
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/dnaidoo621/htpc-remote
Description: Self-hosted HTPC remote control (Glide)
 Point your phone camera at the QR code that appears on screen and control
 your HTPC from any browser — no app install required.
 .
 Features: glassy Glide UI, trackpad + scroll strip, media controls,
 app launcher, D-pad navigation, text input, and system settings.
 Supports both X11 (pynput) and Wayland (evdev/uinput) with automatic
 session-type detection at startup.
 .
 Runs as a systemd user service that starts automatically on login.
